The point of this is not to argue whether miners should use renewables over other resources, such as natural gas. But to point out the opportunity in the inevitable.

The use of solar and wind power is happening whether we like it or not, and #Bitcoin miners can ride the wave.

#Bitcoin miners can also hedge themselves against periods when their operations must be turned off by purchasing power generation assets through the financial market. 

That way they‚Äôre always earning steady paychecks from these financial assets when operations are ceased.

#Bitcoin miners co-located next to these wind power plants can immediately power on and begin consuming the excess energy - and potentially all of it.

Miners can either consume the energy until they must shut down, or until they reach their break-even point of profitability.

As a result, they will need to be co-located with efficient battery storage devices and flexible demand-response systems.

Enter #Bitcoin miners, effectively, as the most flexible, scalable and economically viable demand-response resource to renewable energy power systems.

This inevitable trend towards renewable energy is happening, and it poses an opportunity for growth in #Bitcoin mining.
